DIGEST
SB 335 Original 2026 Regular Session Jackson-Andrews
Present law requires the Legislative Budgetary Control Council to establish and implement
a salary schedule for legislative assistants and to make adjustments as necessary.
Proposed law retains present law but authorizes the Legislative Budgetary Control Council
to increase the annual allocation for assistants of a legislator whose district is comprised of
all or a part of more than three parishes to include an additional amount per year to be
determined by the Legislative Budgetary Control Council for each parish in excess of three
parishes comprising the legislative district.
Proposed law provides that this additional allocation is not to be considered as an increase
in or used to calculate the base salary of legislative assistants.
Present law provides that if a legislator employs more than one legislative assistant, the total
salary for all his legislative assistants is not to exceed the base salary established by the
Legislative Budgetary Control Council plus the equivalent of one step for each year of
employment as a legislative assistant of the legislative assistant receiving the highest salary,
or the equivalent of one step for each year of the employing legislator's service as a
legislator, at the option of the employing legislator.
Proposed law retains the present law but provides that the additional allocation per year for
each parish in excess of three parishes in the legislative district does not increase the base
salary of a legislative assistant but is to be used only for additional legislative assistants.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Amends R.S. 24:31.5)
